    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-04-07T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-04-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="1505"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1505">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.51/427.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 17.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Managua</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-07">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 7, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to enclose herewith three copies
                    of the Official Gazette, dated March 30, 1912, containing Spanish text of the
                        <pb facs="1216" n="1100" xml:id="pg_1100"/> new currency law<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d1505fn1">Not printed.</note> enacted by the National Assembly of
                    Nicaragua on March 20, 1912, as reported in my telegram of that date. I am also
                    transmitting a copy of a letter<note n="1" xml:id="d1505fn2">Not printed.</note>
                    addressed to me by Mr. Conant, the currency expert, with its enclosure of the
                    English text of said law as prepared by the bankers who have the loan and
                    monetary matters in charge.</p>
                <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">George T. Weitzel.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
